ollects less. And the \u221213.84% drawdown is a bit surprising; it likely reflects the wing legs being expensive relative to the small net credit, so one bad day hits the smaller P&L base harder in percentage terms. Essentially you paid for insurance you didn't need this month.\n\nThe honest takeaway: **in this calm sample, the naked straddle dominated.** The butterfly only earns its keep if there's a big adverse move that would have blown up the naked straddle \u2014 and June 2026 didn't have one, so we're not seeing the protection pay off.\n\nWant me to:\n1. **Sweep the wing width** to see if a wider/tighter wing improves the butterfly, or\n2. Test both across the **full Mar\u2013Jun range** so we get a month with a real move and can see the butterfly's protection actually matter?", "results": [{"label": "Iron Butterfly", "res": {"strategy": "Iron Butterfly", "metrics": {"n": 21, "win": 66.7, "avgw": 2.02, "avgl": -3.66, "pf": 1.1, "exp": 0.12, "avg_bars": 1.0}, "performance": {"equity_curve": [{"date": "2026-06-01", "equity": 58379.0}, {"date": "2026-06-02", "equity": 53377.0}, {"date": "2026-06-03", "equity": 53380.0}, {"date": "2026-06-04", "equity": 53481.0}, {"date": "2026-06-05", "equity": 53981.0}, {"date": "2026-06-08", "equity": 54888.0}, {"date": "2026-06-09", "equity": 61005.0}, {"date": "2026-06-10", "equity": 61333.0}, {"date": "2026-06-11", "equity": 61333.0}, {"date": "2026-06-12", "equity": 61005.0}, {"date": "2026-06-15", "equity": 61275.0}, {"date": "2026-06-16", "equity": 65081.0}, {"date": "2026-06-17", "equity": 65341.0}, {"date": "2026-06-18", "equity": 65998.0}, {"date": "2026-06-19", "equity": 66632.0}, {"date": "2026-06-22", "equity": 67893.0}, {"date": "2026-06-23", "equity": 60259.0}, {"date": "2026-06-24", "equity": 59970.0}, {"date": "2026-06-25", "equity": 60545.0}, {"date": "2026-06-29", "equity": 59661.0}, {"date": "2026-06-30", "equity": 61059.0}], "final_equity": 61059.0, "total_return_pct": 2.62, "max_drawdown_pct": -13.84, "max