": {"start": "2026-06-01", "end": "2026-06-30", "entry_time": "09:20", "exit_time": "15:15", "lot_size": 65, "square_off": "one"}}], "cost": {"usd": 0.07703475, "in_tokens": 16707, "out_tokens": 725, "llm_calls": 2, "backtests": 1}}, {"role": "user", "content": "Okay do you remmeber what was the first question I asked in this chat session ?"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "Yes \u2014 your first question in this session was:\n\n**\"Test a short straddle on Nifty for June 2026, entry 9:20 exit 15:15.\"**", "results": [], "cost": {"usd": 0.05204125, "in_tokens": 8375, "out_tokens": 50, "llm_calls": 1, "backtests": 0}}, {"role": "user", "content": "Backtest a custom position: sell ATM CE and ATM PE, plus buy a 5-rupee CE and 5-rupee PE as hedges, for June."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "I want to clarify one thing before I run it: **\"5-rupee CE/PE hedge.\"**\n\nThe custom leg builder picks strikes by one of these modes: `atm_point` (points from ATM), `atm_pct`, `width`, `cp` (closest premium), or `cp_sp`. There's no \"5 rupees away\" \u2014 so \"5-rupee hedge\" most likely means:\n\n- **(A)** Buy the CE and PE whose **premium \u2248 \u20b95** (cheap far-OTM wings) \u2192 that's `cp` mode with target premium 5. This is the sensible reading \u2014 deep-OTM tail hedges, basically an iron fly with very cheap wings.\n- **(B)** Buy wings **5 points** away from ATM (that'd be almost the same strike as ATM \u2014 doesn't make sense as a hedge).\n\nI'll go with **(A): buy the ~\u20b95-premium CE and PE as tail hedges.** Running that now.Custom position \u2014 short ATM straddle + ~\u20b95-premium CE/PE tail hedges, June 2026:\n\n| Metric | This (hedged) | Naked Straddle | Iron Butterfly |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Trades | 21 | 21 | 21 |\n| Win % | 66.7% | 66.7% | 66.7% |\n| Total P&L | **\u20b911,564** | \u20b910,776 | \u20b91,559 |\n| Return | **+7.79%** | +4.14% | +2.62% |\n| Max drawdown | \u22126.05% | \u22124.82% | \u221213.84% |\n\n**Assumptions:** ATM CE + PE sold, plus bought the CE and PE whose premium was closest to \u20b95 (deep-OTM tail hedges), 1 lot each, 09:20\u219215:15, square-off \"one\", no per-leg SL.\n\n**Honest read:**\n- This is the **best P&L of the three** \u2014 and notably beat the naked straddle. The \u20b95 wings are so cheap they barely cost anything, so you kept almost the full straddle credit *and* capped tail risk. That's exactly the appeal of a \"cheap wing\" iron fly vs. the standard butterfly (whose wider, pricier wings crushed returns above).\n- Why higher than the naked straddle? On a small P&L base, the return % differences are sensitive \u2014 the wings likely helped on one or two intraday dips. Don't over-read a \u20b9788 edge over 21 trades; it's within noise.\n- Drawdown ticked up slightly vs. naked (\u22126.05% vs \u22124.82%), which is a bit odd for a hedged position but again \u2014 small sample, small numbers.\n\n**Big caveat:** still just **21 trades in one calm month.** The whole point of \u20b95 wings is to save you on a crash/gap day, and June didn't have one \u2014 so we're not actually seeing the protection tested here. To know if these cheap hedges are worth it, run it over the **full Mar\u2013Jun range** (a month with a real move). Want me to do that?", "results": [{"label": "Custom position", "res": {"strategy": "Custom position", "metrics": {"n": 21, "win": 66.7, "avgw": 1.56, "avgl": -2.01, "pf": 1.55, "exp": 0.37, "avg_bars": 1.0}, "performance": {"equity_curve": [{"date": "2026-06-01", "equity": 145496.0}, {"date": "2026-06-02", "equity": 140946.0}, {"date": "2026-06-03", "equity": 140104.0}, {"date": "2026-06-04", "equity": 142028.0}, {"date": "2026-06-05", "equity": 144680.0}, {"date": "2026-06-08", "equity": 147813.0}, {"date": "2026-06-09", "equity": 154300.0}, {"date": "2026-06-10", "equity": 155759.0}, {"date": "2026-06-11", "equity": 157101.0}, {"date": "2026-06-12", "equity": 154920.0}, {"date": "2026-06-15", "equity": 155453.0}, {"date": "2026-06-16", "equity": 15